deck: William Dale Jennings (October 21, 1917 – May 11, 2000) was an American LGBT rights activist, playwright and author of The Ronin, which was adapted as a graphic novel by Chris Dickens and Lionheart Comics in 2017. His novel, The Cowboys, was adapted for film and starred John Wayne and Colleen Dewhurst.
description: Jennings wrote and published his first novel, The Ronin, retold from an ancient Buddhist story, followed by The Sinking of the Sarah Diamond. Another book, The Cowboys, based on a film treatment he sold to Warner Bros. The Cowboys was made into a film in 1972, starring John Wayne.
name: William Dale Jennings

deck: Roho was born in Montevideo, Uruguay, and immigrated to the United States in his early adulthood. Shortly after moving to Cambridge in 2008, he joined Boston Comics Roundtable. Roho has contributed to the last three issues of Inbound, to Show and Tell, The Greatest Comics Anthology of all Time and In a Single Bound as well as publishing and editing Outbound: The Science Fiction Comics Anthology and the five issues of Hellbound Annual Horror Anthology for the last five years, he is working on new comics...
name: Roho
